President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Frank T. Brogan of Pennsylvania as the Assistant Secretary of Education for Elementary and Secondary Education. Brogan has a background in education, having served as a fifth grade teacher, dean of students, assistant principal, principal, superintendent, and Florida's Commissioner of Education. He also served as Lieutenant Governor of Florida and president of Florida Atlantic University. Brogan holds a bachelor's degree in education from the University of Cincinnati and a master's degree in education from Florida Atlantic University.

Trump also intends to nominate Lisa Gordon-Hagerty of Virginia as the Under Secretary for Nuclear Security at the Department of Energy. Gordon-Hagerty is currently the president of Tier Tech International, Inc., a national security consulting company, and president of LEG Inc., which provides strategic advice on domestic and national security issues. She has previously held positions in the White House National Security Council staff, the U.S. Department of Energy, and the U.S. House of Representatives Committee on Energy and Commerce. Gordon-Hagerty holds a Master of Public Health degree in health physics and a Bachelor of Science degree from the University of Michigan.